#math 
> [[3-21-22 Notes - Barycentric Coordinates|3-21-22 Notes - Barycentric Coordinates]], [[Barycentric Coordinates|Barycentric Coordinates]]

We can describe it basically the same as a line!

$$
\boxed{
\begin{align}
X = a\cdot A + b\cdot B + c \cdot C \\
a + b + c = 1
\end{align}
}
$$
**The point needs to be on the plane still! Otherwise we can't write it as [[Barycentric Coordinates|Barycentric Coordinates]]**
